{
  "stem": "24111.1",
  "chunk_idx": 5,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And a lot of the leaders of this particular party were immediately imprisoned.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 5 SECONDS] I mentioned my father.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "My father was picked up on the street of Vienna on one day.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The-- the Austrian police had Nazi arm stripes and were under the control, at that time, already under-- from-- from German Nazis.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Closed up a street on both sides and took everyone which has-- which had Jewish in their [NON-ENGLISH]-- in the [NON-ENGLISH] cards.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Had Jewish papers.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "You-- you see, in Austria, everybody had to have an-- when you go here to a bank, they ask you for your driver's license as a-- a-- a way of identifying yourself.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But in Austria, you had also cards.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And in a moment they saw that you are a Jew, they-- they threw you in jail.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Matter of fact, they were marked, [NON-ENGLISH], Jewish, [NON-ENGLISH].",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So on a driver's license or identity card.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "It was not a driver's license, it was identity cards, yes.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And an interesting part is that at that time, it was possible to get people out of prison and out of the concentration camps.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "If you could show that they had an affidavit, a [NON-ENGLISH], and a-- and visa to emigrate immediately to out of Austria.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And, for example, my cousin Otto Perl, his parents got him an entry permit to England.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And after two, three months, he was released from Dachau.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And I remember seeing him without any hair, with-- with a view out of his eyes of an person which went through a tremendous difficult time.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And he had to immediately leave Austria.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "My mother was able to get my father free.",
      "word_count": 9
    }
  ],
